column1: Units Sold  -  The gross number of units sold.
Trial Units  -  The total number of free trial sign-ups during the subscription period.

Paid Units  -   This number includes each transaction related to a paid subscription. for example a monthly subscription will be recorded as a paid unit once each month each time the transaction occurs.
Gross Revenue  -  This is calculated by multiplying units sold by the customer's price.
Units Returned   -  These are the total number of units for which amazon refunded the customer's price.
Refunded Revenue  -  Total amount refunded to customers who returned their purchase.
